=E2=80=9D and see what he says.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meanwhile Musk borrowed money to buy Twitter f=
rom his banks. Ordinarily the banks would have sold this debt to investors =
before closing, but given the process here =E2=80=94=C2=A0where Musk was tr=
ying to get out of the deal until the last minute =E2=80=94=C2=A0there was =
no time to do that, and they=E2=80=99re not about to do it now. For one thi=
ng the debt market has gotten worse and they would take a huge loss on the =
deal.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-5" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
