e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">regulatory minimum is 100%<=
/a>, meaning that a bank needs to have liquid assets equal to at least 100%=
 of its expected cash drain in =E2=80=9Ca 30 calendar day liquidity stress =
scenario,=E2=80=9D=C2=A0so Credit Suisse didn=E2=80=99t get all that close =
to the brink. Also you do not have to accept Credit Suisse=E2=80=99s claim =
that the drop was due to =E2=80=9Cincorrect rumors=E2=80=9D rather than cli=
ents=E2=80=99 reasonable response to Credit Suisse=E2=80=99s real financial=
 troubles. Still there is at least an arguable transmission mechanism betwe=
en people posting mean stuff on Twitter and an actual run on the bank.</p>
